{"/service/ndnp/in/batch_in_goldman_ver01/data/sn82015313/00383349217/1929111301/0392.xml":{"full_text":"PAGE 16\nPAPER SUED BY\nFORMER KAISER;\nLIBELCHARGED\nWilhelm Seeks to Have\nBerlin Editor Fined\nor Jailed.\nRu United Pert*\nBERLIN. Nov. 13.\u2014For the first\ntime since the revolution, former\nKaiser Wilhelm has struck back at\nthe critics In Germany, who have\nattacked him throughout his years\nof exile in Holland.\nHe has instituted a libel suit\n\u2022gainst the Berlin paper. Morgen\nPost, which accused him of unduly\nfavoring the Krupp factory in\ngranting munitions contracts during\nthe war. The suit does not ask\nmonetary damages, but seeks to\nhave the editor responsible for the\ncharges imprisoned or fined heavily.\nThe Morgen Post declared the\nalleged libelous article appeared\nOct. 24. It asserted that the former\nkaiser always considered himself a\npartner in the Krupp concern and,\nbecause of his influence, the com\npany enjoyed a virtual monopoly in\nproviding guns and munitions for\nthe imperial army.\nThe Morgen Post article described\nthe kaiser\u2019s alleged pool in the\nKrupp concern as the \u201cgreatest\nscandal in world history\u201d and\ncharged that, because of the un\nsatisfactory armaments produced by\nKrupp works, the German army en\ntered the World war poorly\nequipped and that the kaiser en\nriched himself at the expense of the\nblood oi the German people.\nOne pound of silk is said to be\nthe product of 2,300 silkworms.\nRID OF RHEUMATISM\nAND KIDNEY PAINS\nSays relief came so suddenly it\nsurprised him.\nAfter years of torture from\nrheumatism, back ache and kidney\ntrouble, health has come to Karl F.\nKasch, 834 North Shawnee street,\nFreeport, 111. His letter gives the\nanswer, as follows:\n\u201cI suffered agony for eight years,\nwith rheumatism and kidney trou\nbles. The back ache and the pains\nin my shoulders and legs were so in\ntense that at times I would have to\nstop everything and lie down. I\nwas continually taking laxatives for\nconstipation, but got no real relief.\nI lost weight, had no pep at all, and\ngot up every morning feeling tired\nand worn out. I had tried so many\nremedies I was terribly discouraged.\nBut I finally found the right one,\nViuna. The quick results amazed\nme. The tired feeling vanished and\nmy appetite came back. I began to\nget good sleep and eat hearty meals\nwithout constipation or other dis\ntress. The awful rheumatic pains\nand back-ache left me, and never\ncame back. I have gained 16 pounds\nsince I started taking Viuna. It has\nmade anew man of me.\u201d\nThousands of hopeless sufferers\nfrom kidney trouble, back-ache,\nstomach trouble and rheumatism\nhave been restored to perfect health\nby this wonder medicine. Why\nshouldn't it do as much for you?\nTry one bottle of Viuna under posi\ntive guaranty. $1 at druggists or\nmailed postpaid by Iceland Medicine\nCompany, Indianapolis, Ind\nVI u N r\nThe Wonder Medicine\nHOTHiNO 1\nON CREDIT\nASKtN 6> MARIWE CO\nftl HGTO* tt\nPoor Teeth\u2014Poo? Health\nCu Too Afford to Neglect loartT\nGood Work\u2014-Moderate Prices\nThe People\u2019s Dentists\nM West Washington Street\nHOrRS\u2014R m. to 6 p. m.\nSnndayn\u20149 a. m, to 12 m.\nRent a Plano\nTerm* as Low as\nSI.OO A WEEK\nPearson Piano Cos\nMS-190 N. Pennsylvania\nGOOD AS NEW\nThat dress or suit that you meant to discard can be made to do\nservice another season, all through the magic art of dry cleaning.\nMost of the thrifty people of this city come to us and are satisfied.\nThe cost for Center service is but a trifle and the results amazing.\nWomen\u2019s Men\u2019s ESPS aSgglSjS\nDresses MB Suits C\nand H v and\nCoats O\u2019Coats gfg\nPlain Style* I Cleaned .-j JBh\nCleaned and\nand Preed Tressed mmm \u2019SaSP\u2019\nMEN\u2019S SJf&TQ CLEANED Cft.\nLADIES\u2019 nH I W BLOCKED OU C\nBE SURE YOU ARE IN A CENTER STORE\nOriginator of CASH\nWr and CARRY System\ndslk\nNo. 1\u20141315 E. 30th.\nNo. *\u20145618 E. Wash. No. 3\u20143404 E. 10th No. 4\u20141047 Vir. Avo.\nNo. 5\u20141426 E. Wash. No. 6\u20145365 College Ave. No. 7\u20142180 N. Mer.\nHe\u2019s \u2018Bad Man\nl\n\nWilliam J. (Whitey)' Walker,\nabove, seems to be very much\nwanted by the law in the south\nwest.\nIn jail at Stinnett, Tex., for the\nkilling of three police officers at\nBorger, he \u25a0was transferred re\ncently to Ada, Okla., where he is\nto stand trial for robbery of an\nAda bank.\nWalker, arrested in Buffalo, N.\nY., Jast January, is said to have\ncommitted a number of murders\nand bank robberies in the south\nwest.\nPlane\u2019s Passengers Rescued\nSPEZIA, Italy, Nov. 13.\u2014The crew\nand passengers aboard a French\nseaplane, which was forced down off\nCape Palmeri, Sardinia, were\nrescued early today by the Italian\u2019\ncargo boat Augusto.\nTo End a Cough\nIn a Hurry, Mix\nv This at Home\nTo end a stubborn cough quickly, it\nis important to soothe and heal the in\nflamed membranes, get rid of the germs\nand also to aid the system inwardly to\nhelp throw off the trouble.\nFor these purposes, here is a home\nmade medicine, far better than anything\nyou could buy at 3 times the cost. From\nany druggist, get 2% ounces of Pinex.\nPour this into a pint bottle, and add\nplain sugar syrup or strained\nhoney to fill up the pint. This takes\nbut a moment, and makes a remedy so\neffective that you will never do with\nout, once you have used it. Keeps per\nfectly, and children like it.\nThis simple remedy does three neces\nsary things. First, it loosens the germ,\nladen phlegm. Second, it soothes away\nthe inflammation. Third, it is absorbed\ninto the blood, where it acts directly\non the bronchial tubes. This explains\nwhy it brings such quick relief, even\nin _ the obstinate bronchial coughs\nwhich follow cold epidemics.\nPinex is a highly concentrated com\npound of genuine Norway Pine, con\ntain big the active agent of creosote, in\na refined, palatable form, and known\nas one of the greatest healing agents\nfor severe coughs, chest colds and\nbronchial troubles.\nDo not accept a substitute for Pinex.\nIt is guaranteed to give prompt relief\nor money refunded.\n\u2014Advertisement.\nIlieiY oi\ntUpiMPIESIi\nM Nature's warning:- help nature dear jC\nm complexion and paint red ropes \u00a3si!\u00a3*\nm in yonr pale, sallow cheeks. Truly E!\nm wonderful results follow thorough\nj a colon cleansing. TakeN\u00df\u2014\n\u25a0srf jl NATURE'S REMEDY-to regulate\nJr and strengthen your eliminative or-\nM gans. Watch the transformation.\n3 Try NR instead of mere laxatives.\nJ Mild, safe, purely vegetable \u2014at druggist*, only 2Ss\nf FEEL LIKE A MILLfpN\u2019. TAKE\nEVAN S'\nE r KE\nAT ALL GROCERS\nJ RAG RUGS E\nPopular Hit and oq\nMiss Patterns LjC Each\nECONOMY RUG CO.\nU^*lS^En*^Wa*hlnrtoD^*lri^^^\nNu-Metal Weather\nStrips\u2014Easy to Apply\nCan l)e installed with a hammer and\na pair of shears and without tear\ning out windows and doors.\nVONNEGUT\u2019S\n120-124 E. Wash. SL Est. 1852\nAGED PRINCESS\nVICTORIA, WIFE\nOF YOUTH, DIES\nEx-Kaiser\u2019s Sister Bride\nSecond Time When 62\nYears Old.\nH\u2019l United Peru*\nBONN, Germany, Nc v. 13.\nPrincess Victoria of Schaumburg\nlippe, whose romance at the age of\n62, with a penniless Russian youth,\nended in bankruptcy, died here to\nday. She had been ill about a week.\nThe Princess\u2019 death found her\nreconciled with her brother, the\nformer German Kaiser, who had\nopposed her marriage to Alexander\nZouboff in 1927. The exiled kaiser\nsent many messages and repeatedly\ninquired as to her condition during\nthe last days of critical illness from\npneumonia and pleurisy.\nPrincess Victoria was a cousin of\nKing George of England and was\n64 when she died.\nPrincess Victoria was one of\nEurope\u2019s most-talked-of royal per\nsonages. It remained for Alexander\nZoubkoff, Russian vagabond and\nAttention, Please\nThe \u201cCommander\u201d\nVN. Be Here f 8 Vrjfej\nIT\nWITH\nDIVIDENDS\nSINCE 1669\nEver since 1889, whether securities were up\nor down, whether the business outlook was\nbright or gloomy The Indiana Savings\nand Investment Company has regularly paid\n6 per cent dividends compounded semi\nannually.\nThroughout the United States during the last\n40 years billions of dollars have been lost irh\nvarious other forms of investments, but no\nsaver in this dependable old Building and\nLoan Association has lost one cent of money\nentrusted to us.\nWhy not save here regularly where you\nprofit with safety!\n%e Indiana Savings\nInvestment Company\n140 North Delaware Street\n7 \u201cINDIANA\u2019S FASTEST GROWING DENTAL OFFICE\u201d\u2014--\nV, DR. FORSHEE IS\nSTEPPING UP\nOne of the Most Beautiful Plates high-grade teeth. Dr. Forshee\u2019s\nyj ac le Transparent Light >1 Ex-Cel plate is unconditionally\nSanitary and Almost Indestruct- guaranteed.\nible. nmrr TU AT Each tooth shaded to match\nAT A PRICE THAT vour old ones. Plate is really\nDEFIES COMPETITION face forming.\nPAINLESS R 535.00 $1 7.50\nEXTRACTION/ Value 11\nDr. Forshee s own proven X _ n; j\nmethod used exclu- X TRE MAN \\y HO KNOWS HOW rOWn DTiageS\nsiyely. No charge f 'V 22-Kt Gold None\nwith other f better\u2014per tooth,\n/\u201c\u25a0'\u2022ForsheeX';~\n22V& N. Penn. St. 7 l o'S v s\nFountain Square Office No. 2\n1108 Shelby St. Over Horuff Shoe Store DR. 7360\nr OFFICK XO. 3 AT 38 MERIDIAN ST.. AXHERSON, IXP.\nTHE INDIANAPOLIS TIMES\nher second husband, to reduce her\nto difficult straits, injure her pres\ntige, and wound her heart violently.\nRenounced Throne\nFtom her mother, the Princess\nRoyal of England, who renounced\nher right to the British throne to\nmarry the then Crown Prince Fred\nerick of Prussia, Victoria inherited\na firm belief in love.\nAsa young girl she fell in love\nwith Prince Ferdinand of Batten\nburg, later prince of the Bulgars.\nBut for political reasons the two\nlovers were separated. Bismarck,\niron chancellor of Germany, was\nsaid to have been responsible.\nLater, Victoria married Prince\nAdolf of Schaumburg-Lippe, who\ndied in 1916, leaving her a castle at\nBonn into which she had moved\nfurnishings and priceless hearlooms\nhanded dcftvn to her by her mother.\nAsa Hohenzollem princess, her\nprestige fell with that of the kaiser,\nbut still she managed to reign al\nmost as a queen among her circle\nat Bonn.\nThen at a soiree she met a dash\ning young man named Zoubkcfl,\nwho told stories of the sea and of\nmighty hardships endured.\nForced to Flee\nHe could have told her, if he did\nnot, that he was bom in a little\nRussian tow j n not far from Moscow\nof a \u201cDvorianin\u201d family\u2014the lowest\nof Russian nobility\u2014and that he\nwas forced to flee from Russia in\nthe revolution of 1917 when he was\na freshman at Moscow university.\nIn November, 1927, the two were\nmarried, the princes, 62 years old;\nZoubkoff, 28. Then trouble began.\nZtaubkoff saw no need of working\nwhen Victoria had money. His\nvisits away from the castle became\nmore frequent and longer. Germany\nfound him an undesirable foreigner\nand barred him. did France an\u00a3\nBelgium. He took refuge in Luxem\nbourg.\nHis creditors presented their bills\nto the princess. The former kaiser\nwas highly angered by the whole\naffair. Swallowing her pride, the\nprincess started an auction of her\ncastle furnishings Oct. 15 to pay\noff her husband\u2019s debts. She raised\na goodly sum, but not enough.\nOn the day the sale started,\nLuxembourg banished Zoubkoff, who\nhad been a restaurant waiter there.\nFrance refused to welcome him.\nTwo weeks later he appeared at\nEuskirchen, near Bonn, despite the\nGerman ban against him, and the\nprincess, prodded by the kaiser\nYour\nClothes Will\nThank You!\nTHE\nBEST GRAND LAUNDRY\nRl ley 2555\nserved him with divorce papers\ncharging nonsupport and undue\nfriendship with a barmaid. She\noffered him a large sum for the re\nturn of her letters.\nThe divorce case was scheduled\nfor trial in Bonn on Nov. 22. Vic\ntoria\u2019s death, before that date, leaves\nZoubkoff a widower, still able to\nwrite to the kaiser: \u201cYour affection\nate brother-in-law.\u201d\nThe Smithsonian Institute was\nestablished in 1846 under the will\nof James Smithson.\nFACE BLEMISHES j\nfPfl\nMolrs warts. sores, growths, pimples\nsuperfluous hair, wrinkles, deformi'i\nnose, /oarse pore*, ete.. corrected.\nConsultation free. Send for booklet.\n\u2014Established Here 23 Years.\u2014\nDr. Per Due\nInstitute of Dermatology\nWATCH REPAIRING\nAt Cost of Material\nWATCH CRYSTALS\n,und\nianc.v 49c\nCnbreakable ..J!!!49c\n(leaning (any watch)..... .$1.09\nMainsprings (any watch).. 99c\nJewels (sny watch) *j 19\nRite\u2019s Jewelry Shop\n4* S. Illinois St.\nCROWDS CROWDS CROWDS\nSPECIAL PURCHASE\nSHOE SALE!\nI\"** \u2014Never before in our 50 years in the shoe busi\nness have we ever been able to offer\nI uuiL such values. .just look!\nI Z&S3&? FO *OS I\n/**\"**\u00a3\u00a3\u2014ill\nAll WiZ far*- B\nJBn Wo, k s*\u201e.f RhBBEn\n-47 jjj\u00df\nI SVp G* J\nTHRIFT 1\nSHCe STORE\nCor. Washington and Meridian Sts. Merchants Bank Bldg., Downstairs\nREAD SUICIDE POEMS\nHu United Prett\nNEW YORK, Nov. 13.\u2014The body\nof Ruth Rockwell, the\nPhiladelphia girl, who committed\nsuicide by leaping from a plane over\nCurtiss field, will be cremated on\nThursday.\nExceptional Shade Values!\nInexpensively priced, yet of a quality that is superior, our\nshades represent exceptional value. All are serviceable, made\nfrom durable fabrics and equipped with patented spring rol\nlers. Widths for every type of window. Large variety of\npopular colors to match all nome furnishings. We gladly give\nestimates.\nT>i&6e*yJdon Sha^JShads 2)i/fenu>cs'f\\\nPatterson shade cU\n9 E .WASH. ST.* Phone\u00dfl W 96\n_NOV. 13, 1929\n\u201cWe were all deeply shocked at\nmy sister\u2019s am.\u201d Donald Rockwell\nsaid. \u201cShe appeared possessed with\na depressive and suicidal complex.\nShe read much poetry, particularly\nthat of Sidney Lanier. Lanier\u2019s\npoems about suicide particularly\nfascinated her.\u201d","height":"25437","width":"19176"}}
